No_DT ._.
S.B./379_NN OF_IN 1895_CD ._.
FROM_IN THE_NNP SURGEON-GENERAL_NNP WITH_NNP THE_NNP GOVERNMENT_NNP OF_NNP BOMBAY_NNP ;_: To_TO THE_VB CHIEF_NNP SECRETARY_NNP TO_NNP GOVERNMENT_NNP ,_, General_NNP Department_NNP ,_, Bombay_NNP ._.
Bombay_NNP ,_, 10th_CD April_NNP 1895_CD ._.
SIR_NNP ,_, I_PRP have_VBP the_DT honour_NN to_TO submit_VB ,_, for_IN the_DT information_NN of_IN Government_NNP ,_, the_DT annual_JJ Administration_NNP Report_NNP on_IN the_DT Lunatic_NNP Asylums_NNP for_IN 1894_CD ._.
2_CD ._.
The_DT usual_JJ repairs_NNS have_VBP been_VBN made_VBN to_TO the_DT buildings_NNS during_IN the_DT year_NN ._.
3_CD ._.
At_IN Colába_NNP no_DT new_JJ works_NNS have_VBP been_VBN carried_VBN out_RP ,_, but_CC the_DT usual_JJ repairs_NNS were_VBD made_VBN by_IN the_DT Public_NNP Works_NNP Department_NNP at_IN a_DT cost_NN of_IN Rs_NNP ._.
4,513-15-0_CD ._.
On_IN the_DT 11th_CD of_IN February_NNP of_IN the_DT current_JJ year_NN His_PRP$ Excellency_NNP Lord_NNP Harris_NNP laid_VBD the_DT foundation_NN stone_NN of_IN the_DT new_JJ asylum_NN at_IN Naupada_NNP near_IN Thána_NNP which_WDT is_VBZ to_TO replace_VB the_DT Colába_NNP Asylum_NNP ._.
4_CD ._.
At_IN Poona_NNP one_CD of_IN the_DT male_NN wards_NNS was_VBD re-roofed_JJ and_CC fitted_VBN with_IN ridge_NN ventilators_NNS ,_, and_CC the_DT floor_NN of_IN the_DT back_JJ verandah_NN of_IN this_DT ward_NN raised_VBD 15_CD inches_NNS so_RB as_IN to_TO bring_VB it_PRP to_TO the_DT same_JJ level_NN as_IN that_DT of_IN the_DT ward_NN ._.
The_DT central_JJ building_NN adjoin-_JJ ing_VBG the_DT office_NN and_CC previously_RB unused_VBN was_VBD ,_, during_IN the_DT year_NN ,_, converted_VBD ,_, at_IN a_DT cost_NN of_IN Rs_NNP ._.
481_CD ,_, into_IN a_DT ward_NN for_IN 21_CD non-criminal_JJ lunatics_NNS ,_, raising_VBG the_DT accommodation_NN of_IN the_DT asylum_NN from_IN 106_CD to_TO 127_CD ._.
The_DT great_JJ wants_VBZ of_IN the_DT asylum_NN are_VBP :2_JJ 10_CD ._.
During_IN the_DT year_NN under_IN report_NN the_DT following_JJ amounts_NNS were_VBD sanctioned_VBN and_CC spent_VBN from_IN my_PRP$ discretionary_JJ grant_NN for_IN the_DT undermentioned_JJ minor_JJ works_NNS at_IN Lunatic_NNP Asylums_NNP :3_NNP Statement_NNP No_NNP ._.
III_NNP is_VBZ a_DT return_NN showing_VBG the_DT religion_NN ,_, sex_NN ,_, and_CC residence_NN of_IN the_DT patients_NNS admitted_VBD during_IN the_DT year_NN ._.
Of_IN the_DT 267_CD admissions_NNS and_CC re-admissions_NNS 48_CD were_VBD Christians_NNPS (_( Europeans_NNPS 43_CD ,_, Eurasians_NNPS 2_CD and_CC Native_NNP Christians_NNP 3_CD )_) ,_, 118_CD Hindoos_NNP ,_, 71_CD Mahomedans_NNPS ,_, and_CC 30_CD of_IN other_JJ castes_NNS ._.
As_IN usual_JJ ,_, the_DT majority_NN of_IN Europeans_NNPS admitted_VBN were_VBD soldiers_NNS coming_VBG from_IN various_JJ parts_NNS of_IN India_NNP ._.
Statement_JJ No_NNP ._.
IV_NN shows_VBZ the_DT occupation_NN of_IN the_DT patients_NNS admitted_VBN ._.
Beggars_NNS and_CC mendicants_NNS form_VBP the_DT majority_NN ,_, viz_NN ._.
33_CD ,_, soldiers_NNS numbered_VBD 30_CD ,_, cultivators_NNS and_CC labourers_NNS 29_CD ,_, merchants_NNS and_CC traders_NNS 21_CD ,_, clerks_NNS 12_CD ,_, sepoys_NNS and_CC peons_NNS 11_CD ,_, domestic_JJ servants_NNS 8_CD ,_, and_CC students_NNS and_CC mechanics_NNS 7_CD each_DT ._.
25_CD patients_NNS had_VBD no_DT occupation_NN ,_, and_CC in_IN 48_CD cases_NNS the_DT occupation_NN was_VBD not_RB ascertained_VBN ._.
Statement_JJ No_NNP ._.
V_NNP gives_VBZ the_DT ages_NNS of_IN the_DT lunatics_NNS admitted_VBD according_VBG to_TO sex_NN ._.

4_CD ._.

9_CD ._.
The_DT water-supply_NN was_VBD good_JJ and_CC ample_JJ for_IN all_DT purposes_NNS ,_, except_IN at_IN Ratnágiri_NNP ,_, where_WRB much_RB of_IN the_DT garden_NN ground_NN had_VBD to_TO be_VB left_VBN untitled_JJ ._.

10_CD ._.

IV_NN shows_VBZ the_DT previous_JJ occupations_NNS of_IN the_DT insanes_NNS admitted_VBD during_IN the_DT year_NN 1898_CD ._.
Soldiers_NNS (_( mostly_RB Europeans_NNPS )_) form_VBP the_DT majority_NN ,_, viz_NN ._.
37_CD ,_, beggars_NNS and_CC mendicants_NNS numbered_VBD 25_CD ,_, merchants_NNS and_CC traders_NNS 22_CD ,_, clerks_NNS 17_CD ,_, labourers_NNS 16_CD ,_, domestics_NNS servants_NNS 15_CD ,_, and_CC cultivators_NNS 14_CD ._.
In_IN 36_CD cases_NNS the_DT occupa-_JJ tion_NN was_VBD not_RB ascertained_VBN ,_, and_CC 33_CD had_VBD no_DT occupation_NN ._.
Statement_JJ No_NNP ._.
V_NNP gives_VBZ the_DT ages_NNS of_IN the_DT insanes_NNS admitted_VBD according_VBG to_TO sex_NN ._.
Under_IN 20_CD there_EX were_VBD 15_CD insanes_NNS (_( 12_CD males_NNS and_CC 3_CD females_NNS )_) ,_, between_IN 20_CD and_CC 40_CD there_EX were_VBD 215_CD (_( 183_CD males_NNS and_CC 32_CD females_NNS )_) ,_, between_IN 40_CD and_CC 60_CD years_NNS of_IN age_NN there_EX were_VBD 49_CD (_( 36_CD males_NNS and_CC 13_CD females_NNS )_) ,_, and_CC above_IN 60_CD years_NNS 3_CD (_( 1_CD male_NN and_CC 2_CD females_NNS )_) ._.
Statement_NNP No_NNP ,_, VI_NNP treats_NNS of_IN the_DT various_JJ types_NNS of_IN insanity_NN with_IN the_DT result_NN of_IN the_DT treatment_NN of_IN each_DT form_NN ,_, and_CC is_VBZ summarised_VBN in_IN the_DT following_JJ table:4_NN The_DT following_VBG table_NN shows_VBZ the_DT ratio_NN of_IN deaths_NNS per_IN mille_NN of_IN the_DT average_JJ daily_JJ strength_NN ,_, and_CC the_DT total_JJ population_NN of_IN each_DT of_IN the_DT asylums_NNS ,_, as_IN compared_VBN with_IN that_DT of_IN the_DT previous_JJ year_NN :5_NN He_PRP was_VBD anæmic_JJ ._.
In_IN 1895_CD he_PRP suffered_VBD from_IN dysentery_NN and_CC in_IN 1897_CD from_IN fever_NN ._.
He_PRP was_VBD admitted_VBN into_IN hospital_NN on_IN 17th_CD October_NNP 1898_CD for_IN remittent_NN fever_NN ,_, and_CC died_VBD exhausted_VBN on_IN 22nd_CD of_IN the_DT same_JJ month_NN ._.
The_DT patient_NN who_WP died_VBD of_IN old_JJ age_NN on_IN 16th_CD December_NNP 1898_CD was_VBD transferred_VBN from_IN the_DT Colába_NNP to_TO this_DT asylum_NN in_IN 1886_CD ,_, having_VBG been_VBN in_IN confinement_NN since_IN 1865_CD ._.
On_IN 12th_CD October_NNP 1898_CD ,_, he_PRP was_VBD placed_VBN on_IN the_DT sick_JJ list_NN for_IN debility_NN resulting_VBG from_IN old_JJ age_NN ._.
Before_IN admission_NN into_IN hospital_NN he_PRP had_VBD gradually_RB lost_VBN his_PRP$ eye-sight_NN from_IN senile_JJ cataract_NN ._.
The_DT patient_NN who_WP died_VBD from_IN diarrh6_NN admitted_VBN into_IN hospital_NN on_IN 25th_CD February_NNP 1898_CD ._.
Death_NNP occurred_VBD on_IN 14th_CD July_NNP ._.
The_DT body_NN was_VBD thin_JJ and_CC emaciated_VBN ._.
The_DT brain_NN which_WDT weighed_VBD ._.
43_CD ounces_NNS was_VBD softened_VBN ,_, and_CC was_VBD anæmic_VBN on_IN the_DT left_NN and_CC somewhat_RB congested_VBD on_IN the_DT right_JJ side_NN ;_: its_PRP$ ventricles_NNS contained_VBN no_DT fluid_NN ._.
The_DT heart_NN was_VBD pale_JJ ;_: but_CC its_PRP$ valves_NNS were_VBD normal_JJ ._.
The_DT lungs_NNS ,_, liver_RB ,_, spleen_JJ and_CC intestines_NNS were_VBD anæmic_JJ ._.
The_DT fatal_JJ case_NN of_IN empyema_NN was_VBD admitted_VBN into_IN the_DT asylum_NN on_IN 14th_CD August_NNP 1896_CD for_IN demen-_JJ tia_NN (_( epileptic_JJ )_) ._.
